**Code Explanation:**

This revised script addresses the issues by correctly identifying the job level (HIDDG) and sector (QDB) columns using case-insensitive matching, ensuring that the stratified models are properly executed and included in the final output. 1. Data Preparation: It loads the dataset, selects granular policy predictors, imputes missing values, and standardizes features globally. 2. Overall Model: An overall Elastic Net model is fitted to predict the latent class membership, extracting coefficients for the 'Resiliently Optimistic' class (Class 1). 3. Stratified Models: The script dynamically finds the HIDDG and QDB columns, identifies strata with a sample size greater than 100, and fits separate Elastic Net models for each stratum. The coefficients for Class 1 are extracted and stored alongside the overall model results. 4. Feature Selection & Visualization: The top 20 features from the overall model (plus mandatory features QKB_1_4 and QKB_1_11) are selected. The y-axis labels are cleaned and wrapped using textwrap.fill to prevent truncation. A comprehensive heatmap is generated, displaying the coefficients across the 'Overall' model and all identified strata, and saved as a high-resolution PNG. 5. Console Output: Sample sizes per stratum and the top coefficients are printed to the console.

**Modifications:**

Added case-insensitive column matching for HIDDG and QDB to ensure strata are correctly identified and processed. Updated the results DataFrame to include columns for the overall model and all strata. Implemented textwrap.fill to wrap long feature names on the y-axis, preventing truncation. Adjusted the plot title and figure size to accommodate the comprehensive heatmap.

